        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         It was a Fair comparrison.  I did not do a comparison against 1 lvl 50 Wizzy and 1 lvl 50 Necro, that would have been pointless.  I went all out, except for ancient spells, which really would not have changed the arguemnt anyway.  I wanted to compare the best of the best of each class, that is, the max dmg they could do at any one point and time.  That's why I used the best of both class's spells.</P><P>You can drop aggro in the middle of a fight, Necro's get FD, and Wizzys get Concussion.  Both are effective.  My example may not have been plausable, but it was possible.  EB weapons are more effective than you may think, and There are ways for Wizzys to drop completely off the aggro list without logging, and remain uninterupted in his chain casting.  I just wanted to compare the max possible dmg both classes could inflict, and in the end, the point remains the same Self DoT stacking does not Overpower a necromancer.</P><P>Reepr<BR>Warlock of Lanys<BR><Sigil><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
