        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=63830&amp;TOPIC_ID=7564&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=DPS+and+the+myth+that+necros+are+not+good+at+it&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Ok, gotta correct a few things...</P><P>first. Yes wizards get lures. So do necros... if you haven't noticed, most of our alteration line of spells are lure based. Resists are very rare.</P><P>second. Abitrary suggestions of "increase DoT a to xxxx dmg, then we are fixed" are stupid. You cannot buff up CoC and Splurt and then declare we do more dmg period. I want to do more dmg on longer fights, not do more damage overall. If I want to be a wizard, I'll play a wizard.</P><P>I think there are only a few things left with the necro class which need looking at. That is our role on raid encounters. Luclin went a long way to making our versatility shine on raids like Shei Vinitras, where the whole fight is not a MT/123Cheal affair. But that doesn't balance us in Velious, or Kunark. Or the old world.</P><P>Bottom line, we need a place to shine on raids. Is it damage over time? If so, let us do more damage on the longer fights. Is it mana regen? Then look at how much the other classes have caught up to lich mana regen in the past three years. Is our role on raids still not defined? Then please, define it.</P><P>Verant has never said what they want the necromancer class to be. I think the time has come for Scott or someone to just give us their picture on where they see the necro class heading in the next year or so, so we can decide which of our problems to focus on.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=81496">Dolalin</a> Bonewielder<BR>Warlock of <a href="http://www.theshadoworder.com">The Shadow Order</a><BR><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum">Lanys T`Vyl</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

