			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2522')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=63958&amp;TOPIC_ID=7564&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=DPS+and+the+myth+that+necros+are+not+good+at+it&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I think reepr's point is the most valid here.  We are a damage dealing class that uses a pet until we hit raids.  On raids they have never allowed dots to be that useful.  Yes you can do a good amount of damage on longer fights, but nothing compared with other damage classes (like wizards, and mages if they were not mod rod hoes).  </P><P>We are not and should never be wizards.  Wizards are all about peak damage output over short periods of time then they have a required rest (to regen mana), and repeat.  The next class is about high levels of sustained damage (due to our dots and self mana regen).  This is two different styles of same thing, a high damage output pure caster class.</P><P>Reepr's suggestion has alot of merit to put us back into the damage role we all grew up with (from 1-50) soloing and XP grouping.  SoE would only have to allow the hundred+ slots on the lvl 60+ mobs and could easily leave the less then 60 at 30slots.  There is not reason why the necro class could not get lvl 59-60 poison and disease in the same league has FP.  We have always been a fire, poison disease class.  Yes we can do a bit of cold, but we are not that good at it.</P><P><BR>BTW, allowing necros to get natural dot crits just like wizards get natural DD crits would be a good thing.  It is not going to add much damage but enough to help a bit and would allow us a similar progression that wizards already enjoy.  </P><P>Add to this an AA dot crit skill in arch AA and there is some parity for all dot classes (necro, shaman,druid,...enchanter).</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
